The paper proposes a new benchmark for AI research that involves learning from pixels and a sparse reward signal to solve both low-level control and high-level planning problems in a 3D, 3rd person, procedurally generated environment. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision (cs.CV), Graphics (cs.GR), and Robotics (cs.RO).
